Deputy Chief Justice Raymond Zondo made a statement about the events that took place during Tuesday's evening session when the cross-examination of Minister Pravin Gordhan by Advocate Dali Mpofu got a little heated. Courtesy #DStv403 * This live event has event has ended. You may watch a recording above. JOHANNESBURG - Deputy Chief Justice Raymond Zondo is making a statement about the events that took place during Tuesday's evening session when the cross-examination of Minister Pravin Gordhan by Advocate Dali Mpofu got a little heated. WATCH: State capture inquiry gets heated The commission held an evening session to conclude the cross-examination of Gordhan by former SARS commissioner Tom Moyane's legal team. The session concluded on a heated note, with Mpofu telling Gordhan's counsel to "shut up".